label.value: Decreased proportion of class-switched memory B cells

definition.value: A structural anomaly of the adjacent structures (i.e., adnexa) of the eye, defined as the lacrimal apparatus, the extraocular muscles and the eyelids, eyelashes, eyebrows and the conjunctiva.
Any structural anomaly of the heart and blood vessels.
Any structural anomaly of the muscular columns which project from the inner surface of the right and left ventricles of the heart (cardiac trabeculae, trabeculae carneae).
Inflammation of the vagina that can result from a spectrum of conditions that cause vaginal and sometimes vulvar symptoms, such as itching, burning, irritation, odor, and vaginal discharge.
Any structural anomaly of the tongue.
Any functional anomaly of the tongue.
Supernumerary clitoris.
An anomaly of the electrical conduction physiology of the heart.

label.value: Abnormal morphology of the great vessels

definition.value: A structural anomaly affecting a blood vessel involved in the circulation of the heart, i.e., the superior or inferior vena cava, the pulmonary arteries, the pulmonary veins, and the aorta.
An abnormality of the structure of the pulmonary artery.
An abnormality of the structure of the pulmonary veins.
An abnormality of the function of the pulmonary veins.
A chronic deviation from normal pressure in the systemic arterial system.

A deviation from the normal activity of coagulation factor VIII. Factor VIII (fVIII) is a cofactor in the intrinsic clotting cascade that is activated to fVIIIa in the presence of minute quantities of thrombin. fVIIIa acts as a receptor, for factors IXa and X.
An elevation in bone density in one or more tarsal bones of the foot. Sclerosis is normally detected on a radiograph as an area of increased opacity.

label.value: Impairment of activities of daily living

definition.value: Difficulty in performing one or more activities normally performed every day, such as eating, bathing, dressing, grooming, work, homemaking, and leisure.
Partial or total incontinence of bowel or bladder.
Any anomaly of ovarian function.
Any anomaly of the structure of an organ ofthe endocrine system.
Any anomaly of the function of the endocrine system.
